The most subtle of these morbid humors, those which are the most easily evacuated, take refuge either in the skin or in the extremities of the limbs. They then pro- duce hideous eruptions on those points and these exan- thems soon spread over the whole body and cover the face with a repulsive mask.

Unknown up to our days, these eruptions consist of pustules and conical pimples, which, gorged with cor- rupted liquids, are not slow in opening to allow the escape of a mucous ancl virulent sanious liquid. Even, sometimes, the pimples that are similar develop in the depths of organs and noiselessly corrode the tissues. lt is thus that horrible ulcers are seen covering the limbs, denuding the bones, eating the lips and penetrating the throat‚ from which there only issues a weak and plaintive voice.

At other times, again, there exhales from the skin thick humors which dry into fearsome crusts on the sur- face of the integument. Like these are seen the viscid juices which come from the cherry tree or the almond tree condensing in a gummy callus on the bark of these trees.

Ah! how many patientS‚ sorrowful victims of this plague have contemplated with horror their faces and their bodies covered with the hideous taints, deploring their youth destroyed in its bloom, and have cursed the gods and threatened the sky} Unforrunates!
